 1233
Your Honour, 

I stand before this court today to plead guilty to the offence I committed. I accept full responsibility for the consequences of my actions and acknowledge the seriousness of my offence.

The offence I committed was speeding with my brand-new car. I succumbed to the temptation and wanted to test the capabilities of my vehicle. I must admit, it was a thrilling experience. However, I am fully aware that my actions put the safety of others at risk. I deeply regret the danger I inflicted on those around me and the potential harm that could have occurred.

I must also confess that I failed to respond to the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) sent to me. This was not a deliberate act of evasion, but rather a result of my negligence. I have never been one to pay close attention to my mail, and as a result, I missed the notice. I understand that this failure to respond promptly is an additional offence for which I must be held accountable.

Considering my age of 26, I am aware that I am outside the typical range of offenders involved in this type of offence. Nevertheless, it is important to note that I have no other criminal record apart from the penalty points I have acquired from previous speeding incidents. I deeply regret my past actions, and I assure the court that I have learned from those experiences.

Additionally, I suffer from ADHD, which may have affected my impulse control and contributed to my past driving offences. I understand that this is not an excuse for my behaviour, but rather an explanation of a possible underlying factor. I am actively seeking treatment and guidance to better manage my ADHD and mitigate the risk of future incidents.

I would like to take this opportunity to express my genuine remorse for my actions. I am committed to making amends for the harm I have caused. I am willing to undergo any necessary educational programs or rehabilitation to improve my understanding of the dangers of reckless driving and to prevent the recurrence of such behaviour.

I am also willing to compensate for any damage or inconvenience caused to society as a result of my offence. I value the safety and well-being of others and will do everything within my power to rectify the harm I have caused.

Furthermore, I acknowledge the impact that this process has had on me. The guilt and shame I feel have already inflicted a significant emotional toll. I have had ample time to reflect on my actions and the potential consequences. This process has been a wake-up call for me, and I am fully committed to making the necessary changes to become a law-abiding, responsible member of society.

In conclusion, Your Honour, I stand before this court today to plead guilty to the offence I committed. I understand the gravity of my actions and the impact they have had on others. I accept full responsibility for my behaviour and I am committed to learning from this experience. I respectfully ask for the court's leniency and consideration of the mitigating factors presented.

